column5: Anybody have info on Mink Lake ontario NWO flyin going in late may
good lake, good operator you won't be dissapointed.

We went up to Mink lake in 2001 and had a great time. The cabin was very spacious and lake was fast action. Not many big fish but lots 14 - 18 and good northern fishing. Only camp on lake. Entire system is relatively shallow, especially the two lake to the south. We got checked the last day of the trip via float plane guys and gal were very nice. You will have a good time. Enjoy
lots of perch. walleyes are ok-15-20 inches. smaller pike. have fun
